🔴 High Impact — Strongly Recommended
Imbalanced Data & Sampling Strategies
Sits between EDA and Training — a very common real-world problem with its own full treatment:

SMOTE / ADASYN / Borderline-SMOTE oversampling
Random / Tomek / Cluster undersampling
Cost-sensitive learning (class weights in loss)
Decision threshold optimization (not just 0.5)
Combination sampling (SMOTEENN, SMOTETomek)
Evaluation metrics adapted for imbalance (AUC-PR, G-mean, MCC)
ydata-profiling already flags this — but there's no dedicated treatment phase today
Synthetic Data Generation & Privacy / PII
Two tightly linked concerns that are now regulatory requirements:

PII Detection — detect email, phone, SSN, name, DOB columns before any processing
Anonymization / Masking — hash, redact, generalize, or synthetic-replace sensitive columns
Synthetic Data Generation — CTGAN / TVAE / SDV for: privacy-safe sharing, augmenting small datasets, testing with realistic data
GDPR / HIPAA compliance flags — LM Studio can reason about regulatory risk per column
This is especially critical because the platform ingests arbitrary CSVs — you don't know what's in them
Active Learning & Human-in-the-Loop Feedback
Closes the most important loop: Deployment → Ground Truth → Retraining:

Post-deployment ground truth collection endpoint
Uncertainty sampling — model identifies which unlabeled rows it's least confident about, asks for labels
Annotation queue UI — present uncertain samples to a human reviewer
Label ingestion → trigger incremental retraining
Drift + label drift detection (when the real-world distribution shifts)
Without this, models degrade silently after deployment
🟡 Medium Impact — Worth Including
Pipeline Orchestration & Scheduled Retraining
Makes the platform production-grade rather than one-shot:

DAG-based pipeline definition — declare step dependencies explicitly
Cron / event-triggered retraining schedules ("retrain weekly" or "retrain when drift detected")
Step-level caching — skip re-running profiling if data hasn't changed
Pipeline versioning — track which pipeline produced which model
Failure recovery — retry failed steps without re-running successful ones
This is what separates a demo from a production MLOps platform
Model Interpretability & XAI (Extended)
SHAP/LIME exist today but explainability deserves a full dedicated phase:

SHAP waterfall, beeswarm, decision plots (beyond force plots)
ICE (Individual Conditional Expectation) plots
Global vs local explanation modes
Counterfactual builder (DiCE integration is partial today)
Partial Dependence Plots (PDP) for any deployed model
Regulatory-grade explanation export (required in finance/healthcare)
LM Studio narrative explanations from raw SHAP values
Note: Phase 9.7 touches this but it deserves its own dedicated treatment
Experiment Collaboration & Multi-User
Enables team adoption beyond a single data scientist:

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) — Admin / Data Scientist / Analyst / Viewer roles
Shared workspaces / projects with permission management
Experiment commenting and annotation
@mention notifications and activity feeds
Team leaderboard — compare runs across team members
Audit log — who trained what, when, with what data
🟢 Longer Horizon — Future Phases
